<br><b><b>JOB DETAILS</b></b>
	<br>RITES Ltd. is an ISO 9001: 2000 certified premier International multi-disciplinary consultancy organization in infrastructure sector rendering comprehensive professional services in various sectors including Metro Rail Systems, Railways, Highways, Airports, Ports &amp; Harbour, under the Ministry of Railways.
<br>
<br>RITES invites applications from young, dynamic, energetic and motivated persons of Indian Nationality for the position of ‘Graduate Executive Trainee' (GET) for its different projects.
<br>
<br><b>Name of Post</b>: Graduate Executive Trainee ( Civil Engineering )
<br><b>Vacancies</b>: 30
<br><b>Caste/Community-wise break up of vacancies</b>:UR - 16, OBC - 08, SC - 04, ST - 02
<br><b>Age limit</b>: Candidate must have attained age of 21 years and must not have crossed the age of 30 years as on 1st August,2011
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br><b>Educational Qualification</b>: Graduate in Civil Engineering discipline with 60% marks (50% for SC/ST/OBC candidates) from a AICTE/Govt approved University/Institute. 
<br><b>Selection Process</b>: Written test and Interview
<br><b>About Written test</b>: Written test will comprise of two parts viz. Part I(objective) and Part II(Subjective part)
<br>Part I (objective part) 100 questions, 90 minutes, 100 marks. Part I will consist of questions relating to General Ability, Reasoning, General Science, General Knowledge and Civil Engineering
<br>Part II (Subjective part) 120 minutes, 80 marks &amp; will consist of questions on the subject of Civil Engineering only
<br>
<br><b>Date of exam</b>: 17.07.2011 (tentative date)
<br><b>Examination Centers</b>: Bangalore, Bhopal, Chennai, Delhi, Guwahati, Jaipur, Jammu, Kolkata, Lucknow, Mumbai, Nagpur, Ranchi
